\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 He tapped the side of his nose knowingly, and winked. "Ah, it is almost as hard as changing the world of waking. The personal power of all the inhabitants is hooked into the making of this realm. But you already know the principles involved, this is shape shifting, just as you shifted your shapes earlier. It is simply a matter of whether your personal power can override that of the inhabitants. Mine can. This was not just idle fiddling, the first time was both test and demonstration, this second time was a demonstration for your benefit."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "And that comes with time and practice. I suppose we could be more focussed in our practice."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "It is all a matter of what you want. You both apply yourselves to your martial arts practice. If you spent as much time in waking practicing sorcery you would be better sorcerers. Perhaps those small gods would not have lead you to their realm."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz remarked "So practicing in dreaming isn't enough?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Durathror shook his head. "No, dreaming practice is but the first step. Here you learn the doing of something, the principles involved. Not this realm, but other ones, where there is just your personal power. Then you progress to other dreaming realms where the doing becomes harder, until you reach a point where your power is sufficient for you to begin practicing in waking. To try practicing in waking before you reach that point would set your endeavours back."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "But don't I need a torc first?"}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Ah, this is a common misconception amongst novices. The torc is but an amplifier, you must put something in to get something back. What is more, it is not linear, but something like logarythmic..." Seeing the look on her face, he stopped and explained. "When the input level is low, there is no amplification, but as the input level increases, so the amplification factor increases. Until you reach a threshhold level of personal power, a torc will do nothing for you.}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "None of us actually need a torc to shift, the torc allows us to shift further, and for longer by supplementing our own powers. You will be close to that level before you are given a torc. For a start, you must be able to control the power, otherwise all manner of strange things could occur."}
