\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "Lots of Europeans would take offence at being lumped with other Europeans, they've fought wars over that. Liz, have I ever referred to you as black? As durathror said, you're not black, and I'm not white. Kinda pink perhaps, but not white. I'm part Polish, part Scottish, and part Chinese. And didn't you tell me you were part European yourself? I don't think the term 'racially pure' has any meaning."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 Liz shook her head, but she was smiling. "It's okay, I just get a bit touchy at times. I tend to stereotype you as white, I know I shouldn't stereotype people, that's exactly what we complain whites do about aborigines."}
\par\plain {\f2\fs22\b0\i0 "In fact, as my grandfather tells it, he might have married an aboriginal."}
